name: Yakima County Health District COVID Vaccination Site
info: ***1st & 2nd DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS!!!!***!!!!VACUNAS DE PRIMERA Y SEGUNDA DOSIS PFIZER!!! The vaccination clinic will take place at the Toppenish Flea Market. Masks are required. Please wear clothing which allows access to your shoulder. Vaccinations at this site are reserved for people who live and/or work in Washington State. All individuals 12 and over are eligible to get vaccinated. Those under 18 must be accompanied by a parent/guardian or must get parental consent via video/phone call or paper format. La clínica de vacunación se ubicará en La Pulga de Toppenish. Se requieren máscaras. Por favor, use ropa que permita acceso a su brazo. Las vacunas en este sitio están reservadas para las personas que viven o trabajan en el estado de Washington. Todas las personas mayores de 12 años son elegibles para vacunarse. Los menores de 18 años deben estar acompañados por un padre/tutor o deben obtener el consentimiento de los padres por video/llamada telefónica o en papel. ***1st & 2nd DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS!!!!***!!!!VACUNAS DE PRIMERA Y SEGUNDA DOSIS PFIZER!!!
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp
address: Capital Mall - 625 Black Lake Boulevard Southwest, Olympia WA, 98502
info: This is a single-dose Johnson & Johnson clinic being held at Capital Mall, 625 Black Lake Blvd SW, Olympia WA, 98502 for anyone age 18 and older from 12pm until mall closing. We will be located inside the mall, closest to the Sephora end of the mall and next to the Buckle store. Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with layers, if needed. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
